         <abstract>
            <p>A method for interpolating scattered data is described. Given $(x_i, y_i, z_i), i = 1, \ldots, N$, a bivariate function $S$ with continuous first order partial derivatives is defined which has the property that $S(x_i, y_i) = z_i, i = 1, \ldots, N$. The method is based upon a triangulation of the domain and a curve network which has certain minimum pseudonorm properties. Algorithms and examples are included.</p>
          </abstract>
